{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated reply references specific points from the incoming email rather than producing a generic response.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is the model’s content decision, not just local wiring. A stubbed/mocked model would always return a pre-baked specific reply and hide generic/low-context real-model failures (MOCK-HIDE, LLM-DEP). Not Workflow because this behavior targets one model judgment (reply specificity), not correctness across multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run the real drafting model on representative real email threads and assert the draft cites concrete thread-specific details (entities/questions/commitments) above a threshold, with repeated runs to detect generic-response drift.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The factual consistency check flags claims in the draft that contradict entries in the knowledge base.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The behavior is about contradiction detection quality against KB facts; if that checker relies on model semantic judgment, deterministic stubs can pass while real detection misses contradictions (LLM-DEP, MOCK-HIDE). Rejected Workflow because text asks about a single check step (flag contradictions), not multi-agentic chain correctness.","test_description":"Use real contradiction cases (draft claims vs KB entries) and run the real fact-check stage to verify contradictory claims are flagged with acceptable recall/precision, including borderline semantic contradictions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When the knowledge base has no relevant entries, the draft includes a disclaimer rather than fabricating facts.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Core risk is model behavior under missing evidence (hallucination vs disclaimer). Mocked generation would hide fabrication failures, so real model output is required (LLM-DEP, MOCK-HIDE). Rejected Workflow: only one model decision is being validated (how to respond when retrieval is empty), not multiple agentic stages’ handoff quality.","test_description":"Provide threads where retrieval returns no relevant KB hits, then run real draft generation and assert presence of a disclaimer and absence of unsupported factual assertions across multiple runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The approval workflow blocks sending until the user explicitly approves — no draft is sent automatically.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at module/state handoff boundary (approval state -> send action), so above Unit (MOCK-MISS). Real OS/network/subprocess is not required to catch it; an in-process fake mail sender can assert send is never invoked before approval (REAL-INFRA brake keeps below System). No dependence on model output quality, so not Agentic/Workflow.","test_description":"Wire draft state machine + approval controller + sender adapter with a fake sender; verify send is blocked before explicit approval and only allowed after approval transition.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — read thread, generate draft, check facts, present for approval — works end-to-end for a real email thread.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This explicitly requires multiple steps including at least drafting (agentic) and fact checking (often agentic) in sequence; correctness depends on cross-step handoff and cumulative decisions (MULTI-STEP). Lower levels miss pipeline-level failures where each step passes alone but sequence fails. System alone is insufficient because the key boundary is multi-agentic orchestration, not just infrastructure.","test_description":"Execute the real pipeline on real email-thread inputs: ingest thread, generate draft with real model, run real fact check, then verify approval-gated presentation/send readiness; assert end-to-end artifacts and stage transitions are correct.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.65}}]}
